      <ol class="- topic/ol ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Clean the battery cell covers with damp lint-free cloth. If
necessary, clean and slightly grease the poles and links.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check the tightening torque of the pole screws, see documentation
from the battery manufacture for torque specifications.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check the battery with the rectifier switched on. Measure and
record the voltage of each cell.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Perform one of the battery tests: </p>
            <ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Battery discharge test according to the manufacturerâ€™s
recommendation, see documentation from the battery manufacture. Record
the following during the test: All cell voltages, discharge current,
overall battery voltage, ambient temperature and discharge time. If
wet cells are used, check the electrolyte temperature of the pilot
cells.</p>
                  <note class="- topic/note ">May require a test load.</note>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Battery capacity test to check the condition
of the batteries. See chapter <xref href="Battery_Capacity_Test_CPT_0000350030.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </li>
      </ol>
